comments: Belgium-born Reinhardt lived in gypsy encampments as a child. He became a legendary jazz guitarist, despite the fact that an accident in 1925 resulted in severe burns and left two of his fingers partially paralyzed. Included are performances by the band re-formed by Reinhardt about 1940. The original Quintette du Hot Club de France performances are here.
